<br>
You'll notice two things when you are charmed and casting.  First, you cast MUCH FASTER by at least 30%.  Ice Comet just rips off your fingers.  Second, you use very very little, if any mana - or you regain it extremely fast.  The same thing happens when you go linkdead, you become an NPC caster, so you are a monk as well with dual wielding fist power (or staff power - that's part of why I liked the staff of the wheel, even if I was any damn good with it, I was no danger).  You kick, bash, riposte, parry, etc.  All those NPC monster goodies.  And you cast like crazy without being interrupted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raystonn>Raystonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Defender</span><br>  Posts: 453<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/16/03 7:02:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25975.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Any info on spells you cast when charmed by NPC?</span><hr size=1> Bumping this past the lame spammers.<br>
